<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves -
        Cylinder Head Assembly - Install Fuel Injector
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Install Fuel Injector</title>
        <figure id="f1200464" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2662.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Shoulder Bolt</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Shoulder Bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder Head</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the shoulder bolt and tighten it to the special torque value.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the fuel injector O-rings. Insert the fuel injector in the cylinder head bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do not strike the top of the fuel injector to seat it. Use one of the following methods to
                seat the fuel injector in the bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200465" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2666.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Open End Wrench Method</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hold Down Clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wrench</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Method One:</emph>
            Place the hold down clamp over the shoulder bolt. Use a 16 mm (5/8 in) open end wrench on the lower edge of
            the hold down clamp to seat the fuel injector.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200466" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3346.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installation Tool Method</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Installation Tool</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hold Down Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Method Two:</emph>
            Place a fuel injector installation tool onto the fuel injector. Slide the forks between the hold down clamp
            and the fuel injector head and rest the lip of the tool on the cylinder head. Turn the bolt on the
            installation tool to seat the fuel injector.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200467" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2667.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Fuel Injector Hold Down Clamp Mounting Bolt</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hold Down Clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the mounting bolt for the hold down clamp. Tighten the bolt to the special torque
                value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
